{"TopicId":131923,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Stationary surface base MOD","CreatedByName":"Skylar\u0026#039;","CreatedById":157302,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-12T09:24:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Skylar\u0026#039;","CreatedById":157302,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-12T09:24:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(34,34,34);font-family:\u0027Diaria Light Pro\u0027, sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:300;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:26px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:pre-wrap;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(245,246,245);\u0022\u003EHi, I have an idea for a mod maybe someone will be interested? the thing is to do full stationary bases like KSP\u00A0HQ. u can\u0027t move them. something like\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalstuff.com/mod/165/Kerbal%20Konstructs\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalstuff.com/mod/165/Kerbal%20Konstructs\u003C/a\u003E this, capable of doing since and other bases stuff. just on other planets and without launch pads or maybe very little ones to 0.6m rockets and with limited weight/parts just for the local satellite network. on order to build the base, u need to send a relevant amount of some kind of parts(iron plastic, construct, materials) and other kind\u0027s of parts that can be useful to build the base. to be in that place\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Evanitis","CreatedById":145424,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-12T10:51:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are such mods.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/54284-105-extraplanetary-launchpads-v5295-exp/\u0022\u003EExtraplanetary Launchpads\u003C/a\u003E adds portable (read: very heavy and extrememly bulky) parts that can build stuff from rocket parts that\u0027s smelted from a new ore resource. Fuel for that can be obtained by the stock mining rigs. One needs to build big, complex economies to make it work, but can be done on any planet, moon or on orbit too. You can move these in theory, but it\u0027s tedious enough to get these where you wanted them in the first place.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr if one is too lazy to set up such bases, there\u0027s \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/130318-alien-space-programs-take-ksc-and-push-it-somewhere-else-duna-laythe-or-eve/#comment-2370629\u0022\u003EAlien Space Programs\u003C/a\u003E, that instantly places KSC on Duna, Laythe or Eve.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-12T10:52:52Z\u0022 title=\u002202/12/2016 10:52  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 12, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Evanitis\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Skylar\u0026#039;","CreatedById":157302,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-12T11:26:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-top:0px;color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/54284-105-extraplanetary-launchpads-v5295-exp/\u0022 style=\u0022color:rgb(60,105,148);text-decoration:underline;background-color:transparent;\u0022\u003EExtraplanetary Launchpads\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0I using this one. the idea born\u00A0from it. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topi